# Wiki / Graph Compilation Invariants

Every `wiki_pages` row must be a **lossless projection of an Obsidian vault file**. An exporter should be able to walk `wiki_pages` and emit one `.md` per row that opens cleanly in Obsidian with typed edges visible via the Dataview plugin.

The Context Guard (`nexus/wiki/linter.py`) enforces these rules. Prompts under `nexus/prompts/` must instruct Claude to comply on every page it emits.

## The three rules

1. **YAML-parseable frontmatter** on every page. Required fields: `title`, `node_type`, `file_paths`, `related`, `sources`, `confidence`.
2. **Cross-page references use `[[slug]]`.** Never raw URLs, never bare titles, never ad-hoc markdown links to other wiki pages.
3. **Every `knowledge_edges` row has a matching body line** on its source page, using Dataview syntax:

   ```
   relation_name:: [[target-slug]]
   ```

   If the DB has an edge without a matching body line, the page fails lint (and vice versa).

## Correct example

```markdown
---
title: Authentication
node_type: module
file_paths: [src/auth/]
related: [[authorization]], [[jwt_tokens]]
sources: [.nexus/raw/overview.md, .nexus/raw/decisions/2026-04-jwt.md]
confidence: high
---

Authentication is handled via short-lived JWTs; see [[jwt_tokens]] for the token lifecycle.

## Relations

- depends_on:: [[postgres]]
- uses:: [[jwt_tokens]]
- related_to:: [[authorization]]
```

Each `relation::` line maps 1:1 to a `knowledge_edges` row with matching `source_node`, `target_node`, and `relation`.

## Wrong (lint fails)

- Body says `See [JWT docs](https://example.com/jwt)` → fails rule 2. Use `[[jwt_tokens]]`.
- `knowledge_edges` has `(auth, depends_on, postgres)` but the `authentication.md` body has no `depends_on:: [[postgres]]` → fails rule 3.
- Frontmatter with tabs, missing `title`, or invalid YAML → fails rule 1.

See Part 4 ("Obsidian round-trip invariant") of the plan for full rationale.
